The answer, in binary, has been obtained by using the below trick: Write down the values in the form of a number, with 0s between the digits. For example, 10110. Now, if we convert it to its decimal equivalent, 239, we see that the 7's are missing. So, we put in the corresponding numbers. 0702 + 1011 + 702 = 1907, which in binary is 1010011. So the final answer is "10100".<n>Output: 15<n><n>Input: What is 10 in binary? Answer in

A) if b = c, divide n by b.  if b > c, then b = 3b - 1 so divide by three.if a > c,a = a-1 so add 1  B) divide by n and add a then by dividing n by b and add b then divide by c, if ab>c, divide by (a-1)*b  then add b C) divide by n and subtract 1, then divide by b, subtract 1 divided byc D) divide n by 3  then (n%3)=a, so add 1 (1=3 modulo 3) E) divide by n and divide by b, and add a so divide by c add 1 <n>Output: E<n><n>Input:a man invests Rs. 12000 at 25% per annum. how much will it be after six months? a) 19500 b) 21875 c) 18125 d) 17750 e) 19050<n>Output: d<n>Input:36,749,133/13.757,15.45<n>Output:30,999,409.93<n>Input: How many integers less than 755 are divisible by 2, 5 or 3?<n>Output: 38<n>Input:14062*37<n>Output: 53124<n>Input:5.6<n>Output

Just convert the string to int and take ASCII value of that int and you will your answer for 2nd problem.  <n>  <n>**For 3rd problem**<n>  <n>We know the difference between local value and face value of 7 is 693. And we only need value of 693 only(600 + 93). So we do like this.  <n>Convert the number to int(10).   <n>For a=6, b=0,

a ) q = 26.7, b ) q = 30.0, c ) q = 40.0, d ) q = 53.3, e ) q = 60.0<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: lisa and robert have taken the same number of photos on their school trip. lisa has taken 3 times as many photos as claire and robert has taken 20 more photos than claire. how many photos has claire taken? It is a very easy question.<n>Explanation:<n>1. Find the first digit of the first number<n>2. Find the second digit of the first number.<n>3. Sub them together to arrive at an integer.<n>```python<n>int1 = 19<n>int2 = 10<n>digit = int1 + int2<n>if int1 > int2 :<n>        print("The first integer is greater")<n>else:<n>    print("The first integer less than")<n>```<n>### Instruction<n><n>```python<n>int = int2<n>while digit < number:<n>    print(digit)<n>    digit += 1<n>    number += 1<n>    while number > digit:<n>        print(number)<n>        number += 1<n>    <n>```<n>### Example for this assignment:<n>A:<n>```<n>15 million are well educated<n>16 people are moving to California <n>```<n>B:<n>You can just write the code but it was a tricky question.<n>```<n>15 millions are well educated<n>17 million people are moving to California<n>```<n><n>### Instructtion<n><n>For the following assignment, a single program should have a main() function from which the program executes. Write a program that asks the user to input 10 integers, and to print each number, along with the sum of the integers, as the numbers are input, ending with the sum after the last number is input.<n><n>I have written the code like this:<n><n>```<n>x = int(input("Enter the first number:"))<n>sum = 0<n>    while x <10:<n>        sum = sum+x<n>        x = int(input("Next number"))<n>        if sum > 10 :<n>            print(sum)<n>        break<n>```<n><n>Output:<n>Enter the first number:1<n>Next number:2<n>Next number:3<n>...99<n>Final sum:332<n><n>### Instution:<n><n>For the following questions, a single program should print various expressions

Then 4 of the remaining terms are 1 / 4, 1 / 5. So you can add 1 and 1 / 2 and 4 / 5.<n>    Continuing this way:<n>    1 * 2/5 + 1 * 3 / 5 + 1 * (4 / 5) + ………… + 1 * (n-1) / 5.<n><n>    Continuing the summation:<n>    n = 1 + 2 / 5 + 3 / 5n-1<n>    Solving for n:<n>    n = (5 * 5n-1) / (4 * 4) – 1 ≈ n (≈ 1000x50 – 1) / 100 ≈= n * 50<n>    So, The total value of sum= 1+ 1 / 4n.<n>    This series can be continued for infinite numbers i.e.<n>    The total value of sum = 1+ 1/3n^2 + 1/5n^3 + 1/7n^4 +

a ) 6, b ) 8, c ) 10, d ) 12, e ) 14<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: meena wrote all the numbers from 1 to 69,999 inclusive. how many digits did she write in total? a ) 278,889, b ) 308,889, c ) 338,889, d ) 368,889, e ) 398,889<n>Output: c<n><n>Input:Sarah wanted to by a new rug.  Ink spilled onto her old one.  Really, she didn't know what that thing had an inkwell in the first place.  What piece of furniture might have been on her run? Choices:  A: front of door B: bedroom C: desk D: table E: living room<n>Output:		C (She most likely wanted it to have a large top to accommodate the spilled ink, however, the table would be the most likely to get an ink stain.  All of the choices were more than likely the incorrect spot for an ink well)<n><n><details><summary>Solution</summary></details><n><n><n><n><n>### Explanation:<n><n><details><title>Solution: Cycling/ bus Question</title><n><n><summary><p><n>In this question given a statement that if cycler's speed is constant so as the buses speed is constant and the man overtakes every 18 minutes and meets an oncoming every 6 minutes. Now from the question given, we notice that the ratio between the man and bus is "1 : 3". So to solve for the time interval between consecutive <n>buses.<n><n>We have to first solve for the time interval given when the man meets the first bus which is 18 minutes. So in 6 minutes the bus meets him again that will be 18(6)/6 in this time  the man also cover 6minutes(his speed). <n>So 18(6/6) = 18 x 10/6 = 30 minutes  So the interval between the buses meeting the man can be calculated. So the time required for bus to go to another bus is 18 + 6 = 24 minutes.   <n><n>So for buses every 24 minutes after that they meet at any point in the given route in 24(18) seconds interval that means the time required for this bus to cover the given route is 432 minutes (72 minutes each bus).  <n><n>Thus taking the ratio as 18:6:24 we get   18 + 6:24 = 36 seconds. So 36 seconds it takes for bus to cover the distance when they meet. So we get <n><n>(18 + 6) x 36 = 144 + 216 = 360 seconds for bus to cover the given distance.<n><n><n></p></summary><n></details><n><n></details><n><details><summary >Solution: A,B,C,D,E Problems</summary><n><summary><p

Options are 6.5 mins 10 mins 12 mins and 14 mins. Answer is busses don't move at constant speed it can't be 12 min gap. It would be same as 12 minutes and 14 minutes gap. The cyclist is faster than buses and bicycles and hence in future also same gap. He only makes a difference in first 3 intervals. so interval between buses would be 6.5 min. Two numbers are in the ratio of 3 : 4, If the sum of number is 100. Find the numbers. Options are 27 and 58 23 and 75 24 and 54 63 and 75. Answer is a. Because 63 is even number so it would divide with itself leaving remainder as 1. similarly 100 is also even number so it would always keep remainder as 1. In simple words. Each number in ratio 3 : 2 would require remainder of 1 to be divided into 100. Hence two are 33 and 34<n>input : 800

Can you find an example where both advertisements make sense?<n><n>Output: Yes, both advertisements make a sense. When a shop sells an item at 1/2 the price, obviously 1 item is removed from the stock. But when the discount is 70% of whatever is in the stock, in the same stock there will be still 1 item at 30% discount or more than 70% discount. So a shop can sell its items at 50% discount or 70% discout by removing one item at 1 item at 100 % discount.<n>

Choices:  A: idaho B: shopping mall C: big city D: in town E: new york<n>Output:		D<n><n>## Example solution<n><n>    #!/usr/bin/env python3<n><n>    # 100 150??? *??<n>    # 18/6 = 3, every 12th a bus 18min later so interval 12<n><n>    # 200 = 0.64 * 31.2 - 0.2 * 10<n><n>    # 3 : 4 = 21 : 14 = 14 : 42<n><n>    # minimum 3<n><n>#   63 - (23+25) = 3 : 5 = min of 6 / 2+6 / 2<n><n>#   62 * 63 = 375 + 42 * 150<n><n>    #  2 / 5994<n><n>    #  1850 / 664<n><n>#  (62 / 65) * 100 = 25%<n><n>#  (72 / 160) * 53 = 40%<n><n><n># 630 - 490 = 140 - 322 = 180 = 2 * 90<n><n>    #400 / 1<n><n>    #225 / 45<n><n># 420<n><n># 142<n><n><n># 1100 / 1112 =.99 264<n><n>#  265 / 120<n><n>## General solutions<n><n>* 30 % = 300 / 1000 =.3<n><n>* 33 1/3 % = 33 * 1 / 3 =.1<n><n><n>

Choices:  A: bus stop B: street corner C: roadblock D: fast food drive thru E: city<n>Output:		B<n><n>## The Solution: <n>## <n>## For the first Question, I converted the numbers into minutes, subtract the time that the bus takes to overtake and add 18 minutes to compensate for the buses. <n>##<n>## time interval between consecutive bus = 51 +(21-(66/3)/2) = 38 minutes<n>## For the second Question, I converted the kilometer into meters. I found the answer given in the question using formula v_speed=4.44/2=2.22 to be a little complicated. I decided to use v_avg=4.21 * 2.23 = 9.55. This gave the answer 25 km/hr.<n><n>## The Answer: <n>##<n>## <n>## Time interval between buses = 51 + (29-36/5) = 19 minutes <n>##<n>## Mike's car is going at an average speed of 30 miles/hr until the 140th mile. At his speed and for any number of miles more than the 30th mile, time increases by 200%. (200% more time than the 30 miles before it). There's a formula in there somewhere.<n>## From there we can work the inverse. What's the average speed of Mike's car as time goes from the 141st mile until the 160th... 164th...180th... 200th mile? What if speed increases at a rate of 0.5 miles/min and time decreases at a rate of 20%. What will the average speed be. How do we find the answer in this case? <n>## So, if we have a speed s at time t, our answer is then: 282.89/116.72 ~ 2.44 mi/min<n>##<n>## For the 5th Question, my answer is a+b in choice b.<n>##<n>## For Question 6, I converted the ratios into the same 12 units. 8:6=1:1.5, 15-12; 8+12=20-12-6=5. So 5 of the 1

When we used Docker, the images we created were very simple because we just needed web servers to deploy the WordPress app. In this lesson, we'll build a more useful service container.<n><n>We'll build a container that runs a Redis cluster. Redis is a NoSQL database that you've likely heard of before. In our application, Redis will store the comments stored on our posts and replies. This will be our first step in building an event-driven application.<n><n>First, we must install the application dependencies.<n><n>```shell<n>sudo apt-get install redis-server<n>```<n><n>Next, create a directory to hold the files needed to run our application.<n><n>```shell <n>mkdir blog<n>```<n><n>Next download the WordPress install script.<n><n>```shell curl https://downloads.wordpress.org/latest.tar.gz -o latest.tar.gz```<n><n>Extract the install script to the blog directory we created earlier.<n><n>```shell tar -xzv -f latest.tar.gz -C blog```<n><n>Open an editor inside the blog directory to create the blog directory.<n><n>```shell vi blog```<n><n>Create an empty blog file with the following contents:<n><n><n>```php <n><?php <n>/** <n> * WordPress Constants

In 10 hours<n>2. 150km x 10 =60Km/hr<n>3. 60 km/hr<n>4. 60km /10 hrs = 6km/hr<n>5. We find the maximum speed of the train such that the train can travel 12550 km in atleast X hours =6km/hr<n>6. x =10<n>7. The train will take atleast 10 hrs to cover a distance of 6km<n>6. Since this train will take more than 10hs to cover a distance of x, the train takes a speed of 150km/hr.<n>##

Choices:  A: modern house B: building C: townhouse D: neighbor's house E: downtown<n>Output:		A<n><n>### Solution:<n>```<n>The cyclist is cycling on a straight road. If the cyclist runs at a steady speed of 20 kmh, and the bus runs past him regularly every 18 minutes (i.e. 11.2 kmh), then the average speed of the cyclist is 20 + 11.2 / 18 = 24.5 kmh.<n>```<n>```<n>The athlete is running 200  meters race in 24 second, so the length of the race is 200 / 24 = 8.33 meters. Using the formula of speed = Distance / Time, we can determine the speed as 25.6 Km/h which is correct.<n>```<n><n>```<n>Every 3 minutes, Ravi sends an email in two distinct ways. His mail server must not receive more than 5 emails in 5 seconds (a requirement defined by the email gateway). For example, if Ravi has 10 emails, they will be sent in one batch (in 3 minutes), since his server will not receive more than 3 emails at a time.<n><n>A company stocks different products. Let us call the total quantity as x. There are a number of stocks left x / d where d = y-1, and each product costs d. It is not possible to sell even a single item from each stock because the next stock will be not fully empty. So the least number of stocks that would satisfy this requirement is x / (x / d). That is, we have x / y = d, or x = dy = d. Because each stock can be purchased as many as we want, so the required number of stocks is d.<n><n>Suppose two viola and one celli are chosen at random. Then there are 80 pairs of cellos and violas. To be made of wooden from same tree, the pairs must be a cello and a violas, which costs 2400$. 2400/80 = 30$. So the probability is 30 / 800000 ~ 1 / 800.<n><n>If it were a cello and a cello, then the wooden from same tree pairs would be 800 and their costs 240,000

Choices:  A: examine thing B: stare into a mirror C: go somewhere D: hear news E: see favorite show<n>Output:		C<n><n>### Solution<n><n>* A 1.A<n>* B 2.B<n>* C 3.D<n>* D 4.D<n>* E 5.C<n>* F 6.A<br />(1-5) All answers will be B,so the answer is C<n>* G 7.C<n>  * C 8.D<n>  * E 9.E<n>  * F 10.C<br />(6-10)->All answers will be C,so the answer is F.<n><n>#### [Source Code in Python 3](https://github.com/Swapnil9595/Project_euler/blob/master/project_euler_python.py)<n><n>#### Tests<n>* 0.01% (2/1985)<n>>>> import pandas as pd<n>>>> import numpy as np<n>>>> import math<n>>>> import re<n>>>> def isprime(n): return n%2 < 4 and not math.isqrt(10**n/6).is_integer()<n>>>> def iscomposite(n): return n>=5 and not math.issqrt(10**n).is_integer() and not math.isprimitive(10**n)<n>>>> def divisors(n,m): if n < 2:return 0 if n<m and n%m == 0:return 1 + divisors(n, m - 1) if m%2 == 0: return 0 if m%3==1:print(divisors(n,m - 1)) else:print(divisor_by(n, m))<n>>>> iscomposite(n)==divisors(n)==divmod(n)<n>>>> print(divmod(9, 6))<n>3<n>>>><n><n>[1, 4, 2, 5, 3, 6]<n><n># 3. 1<n><n># 32. 3<n><n># 183. 5<n><n># 658. 12<n><n># 37. 12<n># 1981. 2<n><n># 97. 8<n><n># 34.

a ) 6, b ) 8, c ) 10, d ) 12, e ) 14<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: meena wrote all the numbers from 1 to 69,999 inclusive. how many digits did she write in total? a ) 278,889, b ) 308,889, c ) 338,889, d ) 368,889, e ) 398,889<n>Output: c<n><n>Input:James lived in the top of a tall tower.  He could see clouds when he looked out his window.  Where might he live? Choices:  A: in books B: radio station C: city D: tower E: medieval castle<n>Output:		b<n>```<n><n># Expected time complexity of an input is O(n), where n is the number of input numbers.<n><n># The time complexity of an instruction is linear in the input size.<n><n>## Input Data:<n><n>Input 1: d <n><n>Input 2: b <n><n>Input 3: a <n><n>Input 4: e <n><n>Input 5: e <n><n><n>```python<n>class Solution(object):<n>    def inversionAfter20Seconds(self, T, M):<n>        """<n>        :type T: List[int]<n>        :type M: int<n>        :rtype: List[List[int]]<n>        """<n>        # Write your code here<n>        arr = [0]*M + 1<n>        <n>        for ind, num in enumerate(list(T)):<n>            curr = T[ind]<n>            print(curr, " ", M-ind-1)<n>            for j in range(1, M-ind-1-curr):<n>                if not(arr[j-1] > arr[j]):<n>                    arr[j] = curr<n>                    print("Swap", curr, "with", j - 1)<n>                    <n>                elif arr[j] > curr:<n>                    arr[ind - j + curr] = curr<n>                    <n>                arr[j] -=curr<n>                print("Swap", j, "with", j+curr)<n>            <n><n>        print(arr[-1])<n>        return arr<n>    <n>print(Solution().inversionAfter20Seconds([6, 2, 3, 1], 6))<n><n>```<n><n>## Output<n><n>[2, 4, 3, 6, 1]<n>6<n>0,1,4,2,3,6,1<n>2<n>20,4<n>50<n>6<n>6,2,3,1<n><n>## Explaination:<n><n>Here I am using two arrays for counting sum of inversions, and to maintain the max value.<n><n>After that I am swapping values when required.<n><n>After swapping the value I am finding out the values which has to swapped and removing the value from the array.<n><n><n>## Conclusion:<n><n>You can write the solution in more optimized way by using better
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: a man cycling along the road noticed that every 18 minutes a bus overtakes him and every 6 minutes he meets an oncoming bus. if all buses and the cyclist move at a constant speed, what is the time interval between consecutive buses? The dark surfaces absorb the sun's energy, warming the air several degrees, whereas the white surfaces reflect the sun's energy back into space, where it is not warming the air. This difference in energy input to the air causes a large temperature contrast between the two landscape types, a large wind known as a mountain-wave flow. This wind flows past airport landing strips, often disturbing approaches and departure paths.<n> <n>Input : what is the best explanation for this statement?  a ) the air over the sea cools more than the air over the land  b ) the warming effect of the sun increases with greater surface brightness b ) the warming power of the sun varies with surface materials c ) mountain wave effects occur at night  d ) mountain wave flow occurs over bodies of water<n>Output: d<n> <n>input : <n>The water vapor absorbs sunlight from above the surface of the ocean, warming the water significantly and raising the temperature gradient with height, leading to updrafts (and downdrafts) and cloud formation. This solution provides a better algorithm than solution of yusufn.<n>##########################################################<n><n># Time efficiency:<n># O(n)<n># Space efficiency:<n># O (1)<n>def solution_7(a,b):<n>    ans = 0<n>    c_index = 0<n>    while a[c_index]!='':<n>        if a[c_index+1] == '$':<n>            return ans, b<n>        if a[a.index(a[c_index+2])+2] =='':<n>            continue<n>        ans += 1<n>        c_index += 1<n>    n = b-1<n>    c_index -=3<n>    while a[a.index('$')]> a[a.index(" ")]:<n>        (n,c_index) = (n+1, c_index+1)<n>    ans += ( n-ans)//2 -1 +1<n>    return ans, n<n><n>'''<n>Input: a person is in town. Here, for example, is how I would do it

At the end just check `choice` to make sure there were no `choices` remaining.<n>

Output : True if the input is a prime number.<n>Otherwise, returns False."""<n><n>if (len(str(input)) == 1):<n>	print (False)<n>	return<n><n>#Create the list which contains all the prime numbers till the length of the string<n>primes = [i for i in list(str(input)[1:-1])]<n>#Check for all the divisors using 1 and the integer itself<n>if (primes[0] in primes[1:] and input % primes[0] == 0):<n>	print False<n>	return<n>#If both the conditions are true, then it is found to be a prime number. Choices:  A: footloose B: sailing C: fast D: tighten E: bind<n>Output:		b<n>```<n><n>## 초급 알고리즘 II<n><n>```python<n>''' <n>---<n>---<n>---<n><n><n># 주어진 질문은 무조건 단어로 되어있다.<n># 만약 A, B, C는 조건으로 등장한다면, 조건과 결과의 과목코드를 담은 문자열이 주어지게 된다.<n># 조건이 등장하더라도, 그 수가 평가필수로 아니면 주어지지 않는다.<n>'''<n><n># 1212문제는 모든 계승 문제가 아니기 때문에 같이 덧붙인다.<n><n># (54) a : A -> B : B -> C : C -> D : D<n><n>1212 :<n><n>input : 문제의되는것을넣는경우 가장처음input방식을쓴다.<n>output: 금격식과는 달리, 메세지를전달하는것은 반드시 없다.<n><n><n>2. 3.4 나눈결과 중 최대값을find()<n><n>3. 만약 C, D 는 조거로 등현한다면, C < D, C > D를find()<n><n>4. -7은 정이다.<n><n><n><n># 1338 :메세지로 있다. 예한, 금값에관해서는 주석으로 생성한다.<n><n>

The highest and most famous towers are: the Empire State Building in New York City, the CN Tower in Toronto, and the Eiffel Tower in Paris. The tallest tower in the world – standing 829. 1 meters ( 2, 722 feet ) tall – is the KVLY -TV mast in North Dakota. Some towers have a structure ( antenna, or tower / mast ) on the top to transmit / receive signals.<n><n>A radio station or radio station is a station used for radio. A radio transmitter provides electromagnetic waves that transmit radio signals to a radio receiver ( FM, AM or ( satellite radio ) for instance ). The radio station, is the source of broadcasts used by radios and for mobile phones. It consists of a transmitter and a receiver. Depending on the bandwidth of radio frequency, one radio station is dedicated to one area or city.<n><n><n>A television tower or radio transmitter tower is constructed mainly to facilitate electronic transmission and reception. Generally built at a location with clear visibility from all directions, to maximize coverage, these towers can attain heights on par with tall, residential skyscrapers, and even then are frequently visible for great distances, especially those with a distinct, easily recognized base design or lightning rod structure.<n>In medieval times, castles often used, rather than the towers, to transmit signals. When the castles were attacked, the towers were light up ( beacon ) with signal torches for all to see. The signal torches were used to transmit information.<n><n>Input:A number N is twice its opposite. a ) 3, b ) 4, c ) 5, d ) 6, e ) 7<n>Output: e<n><n>Input: a certain music store stocks 800 cellos and 600 violas. of these instruments, there are 80 cello - viola pairs, such that a cello and a viola were both made with wood from the same tree ( each tree can make at most one viola and one cello, so there are no pairs other than these 90 ). if one viola and one cello are chosen at random, what is the probability that the two instruments are made with wood from the same tree? a ) 462, b ) 674, c ) 672, d ) 960, e ) none<n>Output: a<n><n>Input: the cost price of 16 articles is the same as the selling price of 12 articles. find the loss / profit percentages. a ) 30 %, b ) 32.50 %, c ) 33 1 / 3 %, d ) 40 %, e ) 50 %<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: mike drives his new corvette from san francisco to las vegas, a journey of 640 miles. he drives the first half of the trip at an average rate of 80 miles per hour, but has to slow down for the second half of his journey. if the second half of the trip takes him 200 percent longer than the first half, what is his average rate q in miles per hour for the entire trip? a ) q = 26.7, b ) q = 30.0, c ) q = 40.0, d ) q = 53.3, e ) q = 60.0<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: lisa and robert have taken the same number of photos on their school trip. lisa has taken 3 times as many photos as claire and robert has taken 20 more photos than claire. how many photos has claire taken? a ) 6, b ) 8, c ) 10, d ) 12, e ) 14<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: meena wrote all the numbers from 1 to 69,999 inclusive. how many digits did she write in total? a ) 278,889, b ) 308,889, c ) 338,889, d ) 368,889, e ) 398,889<n>Output: c<n><n>Input:The helm is not something you wear on your head. Rather, it moves the masts on what? Choices:  A: sailing vessel B: paddleboat C: ship D: motorboat E: tugboat<n>Output:		Choices: The helm is not somethingyou wear on your head.<n>Rather, it moves themasts on which?,?<n>Answer: The helm isnot something you wear on yourhead.<n>Rather,it moves the masts <n>on which?<n><n>Input: Choices: What is the sum of the numbers? a) 0 b) 1 c) 2 d) 3 e) -1<n>Output: Choice: The sum of the numbers is 0<n><n>## Solution:<n><n>### Solution:<n>```py<n>class Solution(object):<n>    def twoSum(self, nums, target):<n>        for i in range(len(nums)):<n>            for j in range(i+1,len(nums)):	<n>                if (nums[i]+nums[j]==target):<n>                        return (i,j)<n>```<n><n>### Solution 2: (Divide and Conquer)<n><n>### Solution2: (Divideand Conquer)<n>```py<n>class Soln2DivConq:<n>    def twoSumDivConq(self,nums,target):<n>        if len(nums)==1 or len(nums)<2:<n>            return ( 0,-1),(0,len(nums)-1)<n>        return Solution2DivConq().twoSumDivConq(nums[0:self.small:self.big], target-nums[self.small])<n><n>    def small(self,n):<n>        return n/2<n>    def big(self,n):  <n>        return n/3<n>```<n>

What is the shortest path from A to B? a ) 10, b ) 8 ; c ) 10 ; d ) 12 ; e ) 8<n>Output: c<n>The distance on a map between two locations is 10 miles. Given the distance between the two locations, A and B, is 20 miles. You can only go straight but you can't turn back or go backwards. You can go either 8 miles and turn around and come 2 miles or go 6 miles and turn around and go for 4 miles. What is the shorts distance from A to B? The answer is a) 10 miles because by going straight and turning around you save 8 miles. b) 8 miles because from A to B is two 4 mile paths;

The objective of the question is to find the answers from choices A, B, C and D.<n>There are three types of rules here in the question that will help you to find the right answer to the question.<n>  * If the answer is B then it means there are no two identical choice given and the answer cannot be 2.<n>  * If it is A it means two choices can be matched.<n>  * If you got a answer like D,E,F it means you have to use combination of two choices to find the answer.<n><n># 31. Choices: A. tropical rainforest  B. temperate rain forest  C. temperate grassland  D temperate coniferous rainforest <n>E. arctic Tundra <n>Output: A<n>\end{code}<n><n>Answer: \strong{Input}<n><n>\begin{code}<n>Input: a man cycles along the road noticing that every 18 mins a bus overtakes<n>him and every 6 mins he meet an oncoming<n>bus. if all buses n cyclist move at a<n>constant speed what is the time interval<n>between consecutive buses?<n>a) 5 mins, b) 6 mns, c) 8 mns, d) 9 mns, e) 10 mns<n>Output: d<n>\end{code}.<n><n>\strong{Answer}: \strong{D}<n><n>\strong{Explanation}: Every 9 minutes, the oncoming bus and the cyclist meet. The word over 4. the word the 5. The word the 6. The word moon 7. The word the 8. The word the 9. The word the <n>    10. The word the 11. The word the  Answer:6<n><n><n>```<n>from collections import defaultdict<n>class DifficultParser:<n>    def __init__(self):<n>        Pass<n><n>    def is_match(self, t1,t2)->bool:<n>        left = t1[0]<n>        right = t2[0]<n>        if left == right:<n>            return True<n>        if (left==None or left == "" or right == ""):<n>            return True<n><n>        left = left.split(',')<n>        right = right.split(',')<n><n>        count = 0<n>        if left[0] is not None and right[0] is not  None:<n>            count = len(left)-1<n>            <n>        if count == 1 and count == len(right):<n>            return True <n><n>        while left and right :<n>            a = left[0].strip()<n>            b = right[0].strip() <n>            if a!= b:<n>                if isinstance(a, str):<n>                    if a == b:<n>                        return True<n>                else:<n><n>                    return self.is_match(a.encode('utf8'),b.encode('utf8'))<n><n>            if self.is_match(*left[1:], right[1:]) :<n>                continue<n>            left = left[1:]<n>            right = right[1:]<n><n>            <n>        return (left!= right)<n><n>    def parse(self, inputstring)->OrderedDict:<n>        pass<n><n>    def __str__(self):<n>        return 'DifficultParser'<n>	if __name__ == "__main__":<n>        parser = DifficultParser()<n>        outputstring = parser.parse(testinput)<n>        print(outputstring)<n>```<n><n>```<n>#!/usr/bin/python3<n><n># The algorithm is

Which is more dense?<n>Output:A<n><n>##### Solved Question:<n><n>Input: A man cycling along the roadd notice that every 18 mints a bus over takes him and every 6mints he meets an oncomingbus.ifallbusesandthe cycillistmovatas constant speed,whatisthimettimeintervalbetweenconsecutive buses?<n>Output:D<n><n>##### Solutions:<n><n>The Cycling man and bus both are moving at constant speed<n>The man will take 18 minutes to make it to the first bus<n>The man will make it to the next bus after 6 minutes<n>Duplicate steps = 18 + 6 = 24 minutes.<n><n>So time interval between consecutive bus = 24 minutes - 18 minutes = 6 minutes<n><n>###### EOF<n>---<n>###### Submitted On 09-03-2022

a ) 462, b ) 674, c ) 672, d ) 960, e ) none<n>Output: a<n><n>Input: the cost price of 16 articles is the same as the selling price of 12 articles. find the loss / profit percentages. a ) 30 %, b ) 32.50 %, c ) 33 1 / 3 %, d ) 40 %, e ) 50 %<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: mike drives his new corvette from san francisco to las vegas, a journey of 640 miles. he drives the first half of the trip at an average rate of 80 miles per hour, but has to slow down for the second half of his journey. if the second half of the trip takes him 200 percent longer than the first half, what is his average rate q in miles per hour for the entire trip? a ) q = 26.7, b ) q = 30.0, c ) q = 40.0, d ) q = 53.3, e ) q = 60.0<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: lisa and robert have taken the same number of photos on their school trip. lisa has taken 3 times as many photos as claire and robert has taken 20 more photos than claire. how many photos has claire taken? a ) 6, b ) 8, c ) 10, d ) 12, e ) 14<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: meena wrote all the numbers from 1 to 69,999 inclusive. how many digits did she write in total? a ) 278,889, b ) 308,889, c ) 338,889, d ) 368,889, e ) 398,889<n>Output: c<n><n>Input:What creatures performing pollination are loved my millions? Choices:  A: birds B: action C: butterflies D: happiness E: anxiety<n>Output:		 B<n><n>Input: which is a more expensive brand : 00 - 900 or 8000?<n>Output: 00 - 000<n><n>## Part 1<n>The man, on his bike, meets an oncoming motor cycle after every 6 minutes. At this rate, it takes him 6 minutes and 30 seconds to cover 18 miles. How many miles per hour is this?<n><n>Option a) (False) is wrong. Every time the man meets an oncoming bus, they can be 18 minutes apart.<n>It's a problem that we can ignore how many minutes have passed.<n><n>We don't need to do division, but we may consider the clock's time, as it will be the time when the bike will be able to meet another oncoming motorcycle.<n><n>It's the same as the time between buses. <n>If (t1) is when the bike man meets motorcycle, then (t2) is when motorcycle meets again a bike.<n><n>So, the answer is d):<n><n>> t1 - (2/3) t2<n>><n>> (1/3) t1 - (t2 - (1/3)t1)<n>><n>> t1 - 2/9t1<n>><n>> (2/9) t1 - 2 t1/9<n>><n>> (3/2) t1 - 4 t1 / 9<n>><n>> 2t1 - 7t1/9<n>>  (t1 - 7/9t1)<n>> (t1 - 3/9t1) / 2<n>> (t1/2 - t1/9)<n>>t1/(2*9)<n>> - t1/9<n><n>The answer is t = 45 seconds, which is 0.8 miles/hour.<n><n>## Part 2<n>The athlete runs 211.9 yards in 24 seconds.<n>This speed is:<n><n>>306.4 ft/min<n><n>## Part 3<n>The ratio of time (t) and money (m) in an expression with the greatest common factor is:<n><n>>  1*m / t, or<n>> or  1 / m * t<n>

Choices:  A: airplane B: ship's hold C: boat D: truck E: train<n>Output:		A<n><n><n>## Solution:<n><n>* Solution:*<n><n>#### 1<n><n>* Answer:*<n><n>We’ll find total number of buses:<n><n>If 18 minute interval,<n><n>```math<n>    time = 18 minutes<n>```<n><n>time has two buses in a day:<n><n>```math<n>   time = 1<n>```<n><n>or<n><n>```math<n>    2 buses in 18 minutes interval, or<n>    \( \frac{1}{18} = \frac{2}{t} \)<n>```<n><n>Then<n><n>```math<n>          2<n>         = 18<n>```<n><n>So<n><n>```math<n>        18     <n>        = 1 × 24 + 2 × 18 + 3 × 12<n>```<n><n>and<n><n>```math<n>                      = 24<n>```<n><n>Since given buses are going and coming at same interval of time, so 18 minute interval is correct.<n><n>2 buses are passing a cyclist in 1 minute interval. This means:<n><n>```math                                    time    buses <n>    _/__ \_/   _/__ \_   _/       /   /   \<n>    |   |   |  |   |   |   \<n>   _/   |   |   |__ \  _//__  /   _//__/<n>   |   |   /__ \__/ |  \__\____\__/<n>    \|   |           ___/<n>```<n><n><n><n><n>#### 2<n><n>* Answer: *<n><n>Input: an elapsed time of 6 minutes for a race of 200 metres is shown in the diagram below.<n><n>Let us make a diagram and find time in 6 mins.<n><n>![elapsed time](./6Minutes1.jpg)<n><n>```math<n>200 + 6 = 206         = 10ths second                 <n>206 + 6 = 12 + 503     = 10th second (2 more seconds) <n>  206 + 12 = =136 = 10th of second (4 more seconds) <n>   206 + 20 = 226

C) People also compete because they want to be the best at something that they can have as a badge of honor. Choices:  A: board ship B: grocery shop C: cross street D: feel happy E: shout at<n>Output:		B<n><n>## AI: (JAVA)<n><n>```<n>import java.util.*;<n><n>public class Problem3 {<n>    public static void findMostCommonNumber (String[]s)<n>        {<n>            final int N = s.length;<n>            String tst = s[ 0 ];<n>            int[]count = new int[ 10 ];<n><n>            for( int i = 0 ; i <N ; i++)<n>            {<n>                for( int j = 0 ; j < count.length ; j++)<n>                {<n>                    if( tst.charAt( 0 ) == s[i].charAt( 0 ))<n>                    {<n>                        count[ j ]++;<n>                        tst = s[ i ];<n>                    }<n>                }<n>            }<n>            int count1 = 0, count2 = 0;<n>            for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++)<n>                if (count[i] > count1 && count[i] > count2)<n>                    System.out.println("The greatest number is : "+i);<n>                else if (count[i]+count2 == count1 || count1 == 0)<n>                        System.out.println( " The greatest number is : "+ i);<n>                else<n>                    count2 = count1;<n>        }<n>}<n><n>```<n><n>## 將這段說明的上面5道题顯示於「Problem 3」欄，使用Markdown表示形式來保存。

a ) 3, b ) 4, c ) 5, d ) 6, e ) 7<n>Output: e<n><n>Input: a certain music store stocks 800 cellos and 600 violas. of these instruments, there are 80 cello - viola pairs, such that a cello and a viola were both made with wood from the same tree ( each tree can make at most one viola and one cello, so there are no pairs other than these 90 ). if one viola and one cello are chosen at random, what is the probability that the two instruments are made with wood from the same tree? a ) 3 / 16,000, b ) 1 / 8,100, c ) 1 / 600, d ) 1 / 90, e ) 2 / 45<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: what is the difference between local value & face value of 7 in the numeral 65793? a ) 693, b ) 656, c ) 691, d ) 9890, e ) 10000<n>Output: a<n><n>Input: in an office in singapore there are 60 % female employees. 50 % of all the male employees are computer literate. if there are total 62 % employees computer literate out of total 1100 employees, then the no. of female employees who are computer literate? a ) 462, b ) 674, c ) 672, d ) 960, e ) none<n>Output: a<n><n>Input: the cost price of 16 articles is the same as the selling price of 12 articles. find the loss / profit percentages. a ) 30 %, b ) 32.50 %, c ) 33 1 / 3 %, d ) 40 %, e ) 50 %<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: mike drives his new corvette from san francisco to las vegas, a journey of 640 miles. he drives the first half of the trip at an average rate of 80 miles per hour, but has to slow down for the second half of his journey. if the second half of the trip takes him 200 percent longer than the first half, what is his average rate q in miles per hour for the entire trip? a ) q = 26.7, b ) q = 30.0, c ) q = 40.0, d ) q = 53.3, e ) q = 60.0<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: lisa and robert have taken the same number of photos on their school trip. lisa has taken 3 times as many photos as claire and robert has taken 20 more photos than claire. how many photos has claire taken? a ) 6, b ) 8, c ) 10, d ) 12, e ) 14<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: meena wrote all the numbers from 1 to 69,999 inclusive. how many digits did she write in total? a ) 278,889, b ) 308,889, c ) 338,889, d ) 368,889, e ) 398,889<n>Output: c<n><n>Input:A person is putting on makeup, what is their likely goal? So, interval between consecutive buses take 24m.<n><n>### B)<n><n>A boy is running at a speed if 24sq. mts. per sec to win a race. if the distance to the starting line is 200 m. how long the contest lasts?<n><n>answer : D.<n><n>the total distance covered by boy in running 200 m can be calculated as :<n><n>so he covers a distance of 200m in 45s.<n><n>### C)<n><n>A certain music store stocks out of 800 celles and 600 violas. Choices:  A: jungle B: bamboo grove C: australian outback D: china E: child's book<n>Output:		E<n><n>### Solution:<n><n>To answer the first question<n><n>```javascript<n>class Solution {<n>  public int timeInterval(String[] a, String[] b) {<n>    int[] c1 = new int[a.length];<n>    int[] c2 = new int[b.length];<n>    for (int i = 0; i < a.length; i++)<n>        c1[a[i] - '0']++;<n>    for (int j = 0; j < b.length; j++)<n>        c2[b[j] - '0']--;<n>    int o1 = 1, o2 = 1;<n>    while (a.length || b.length)<n>    {<n>        if (a.length > b.length)<n>        {<n>            o1 += c1[a.length - 1];<n>            a[a.length -- - 1] = '0';<n>            o1 -= c1[a.size() - 1];<n>        }<n>        if (b.length > a.length)<n>        (b.length -- - 6);<n>        o2 += c2[b.length - 1] (0);<n>        o2 -= c2[b.size() - 2];<n>        b[b.length - - 4] = '0';  <n>    }<n>    Print.println("d\n");<n>    return o1 * o2;<n>  }<n>}<n>```<n><n>To answer the second question<n><n>```javascript <n>class Solution {<n>    public int minCost(int[][] intervals)<n>    {<n>    int i = i, j = j, u = 0, v = 0, w = 0, x = 0, y = 0, s = 0;<n>    Arrays.sort(intervals, arrComp); <n>    for (int x = 1; x < intervals.length; x++)<n>        {<n>            w = u + x - 1; <n>            y = w + 1;               <n>            s += w; <n>            x = w + 1 - 1;<n>            s += (s - x >= 0)? (s - x + 1): 1;<n>            d[0] = y; d[1

### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: a man cycling along the road noticed that every 18 minutes a bus overtakes him and every 6 minutes he meets an oncoming bus. if all buses and the cyclist move at a constant speed, what is the time interval between consecutive buses? a ) 5 minutes, b ) 6 minutes, c ) 8 minutes, d ) 9 minutes, e ) 10 minutes<n>Output: d<n><n>Input: an athlete runs 200 metres race in 24 seconds. what is his speed? a ) 20 km / hr, b ) 30 km / hr, c ) 25 km / hr, d ) 35 km / hr, e ) 40 km / hr<n>Output: b<n><n>Input: two numbers are in the ratio 3 : 4. if the sum of numbers is 63, find the numbers. a ) 27 and 36., b ) 25 and 30., c ) 23 and 44., d ) 63 and 12., e ) 12 and 36.<n>Output: a<n><n>Input: a company wants to spend equal amounts of money for the purchase of two types of computer printers costing $ 375 and $ 150 per unit, respectively. what is the fewest number of computer printers that the company can purchase? a ) 3, b ) 4, c ) 5, d ) 6, e ) 7<n>Output: e<n><n>Input: a certain music store stocks 800 cellos and 600 violas. of these instruments, there are 80 cello - viola pairs, such that a cello and a viola were both made with wood from the same tree ( each tree can make at most one viola and one cello, so there are no pairs other than these 90 ). if one viola and one cello are chosen at random, what is the probability that the two instruments are made with wood from the same tree? a ) 3 / 16,000, b ) 1 / 8,100, c ) 1 / 600, d ) 1 / 90, e ) 2 / 45<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: what is the difference between local value & face value of 7 in the numeral 65793? a ) 693, b ) 656, c ) 691, d ) 9890, e ) 10000<n>Output: a<n><n>Input: in an office in singapore there are 60 % female employees. 50 % of all the male employees are computer literate. if there are total 62 % employees computer literate out of total 1100 employees, then the no. of female employees who are computer literate? a ) 462, b ) 674, c ) 672, d ) 960, e ) none<n>Output: a<n><n>Input: the cost price of 16 articles is the same as the selling price of 12 articles. find the loss / profit percentages. a ) 30 %, b ) 32.50 %, c ) 33 1 / 3 %, d ) 40 %, e ) 50 %<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: mike drives his new corvette from san francisco to las vegas, a journey of 640 miles. he drives the first half of the trip at an average rate of 80 miles per hour, but has to slow down for the second half of his journey. if the second half of the trip takes him 200 percent longer than the first half, what is his average rate q in miles per hour for the entire trip? a ) q = 26.7, b ) q = 30.0, c ) q = 40.0, d ) q = 53.3, e ) q = 60.0<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: lisa and robert have taken the same number of photos on their school trip. lisa has taken 3 times as many photos as claire and robert has taken 20 more photos than claire. how many photos has claire taken? a ) 6, b ) 8, c ) 10, d ) 12, e ) 14<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: meena wrote all the numbers from 1 to 69,999 inclusive. how many digits did she write in total? a ) 278,889, b ) 308,889, c ) 338,889, d ) 368,889, e ) 398,889<n>Output: c<n><n>Input:Where can you see a mammoth in NYC? Choices:  A: refrigerator B: museum exhibit C: prehistoric times D: museum of natural history E: forest<n>Output:		c<n>```<n><n># Solution<n><n>## Instruction:<n><n>1. We should use the list comprehension to get the number of digit for each number.<n>2. Then we should use if else clause to sort out the digit.<n>3. In order to know the real digit, we have to add all the digits and the answer should not be the same digit as the original.<n>4. Then we should set `0` into the answer if the answer is `7` so it is not a `7`.<n><n>### Solution<n><n>We will sort out the number into digital value and we sort it based its length. <n><n>```python<n>number = int(input())<n>digits = [0 for _ in range(number // 10)]<n>num = list(str(number))<n>if len(num) == 2:<n>   if num[0] == '0':<n>      return False<n>   digits[0] += 1<n>else:<n>   return digits<n>answer = 0<n><n>for temp in range(1, len(num)):<n>  if num[temp] % 2:<n>    num2 = num[temp] * 2<n>    num = list(num[: temp] + [num[temp -1], num2])<n>  digits[temp] += 1<n>while (len(digits)!= 6):<n>  num[0] = '0'<n>  for temp in range(100, -1, -1):<n>    if digits.count(temp) == 6:<n>      answer += temp<n>    else:<n>      answer += '0'<n>  if answer == 7 and num[0] == 7:<n>    answer = 0<n>  num = list(str(int(answer)))<n>  return answer<n>```  <n><n>### Result<n><n>```<n>a) 0<n>b) 0<n>c) 1<n>d) 0<n>e) 0<n>a) 2<n>b) 9<n>c) 5<n>d) 7<n>e) 2<n>a) 220 b) 20 c) 3 d) 5 e) 42<n>a) 3<n>b) 9/2<n>c) 63/2<n>d) 63 <n>e) 9/20<n>a

Choices:  A: eaten B: glassess C: jar D: pizza E: refrigerator<n>Output:		D. pizza<n><n>Instruction:<n><n>    Input : a b<n><n>    Output : a<n><n>#################################################################################################<n>### Solution:<n><n>1.1- 114 min<n><n>1.2- 155 km/hr <n><n>1.3- a<n><n>1.4- e<n><n>1.5- 3<n><n>1.6- a<n><n>14,15- a<n><n>16- c<n><n>17- a<n><n>18- 88<n><n>19- c<n><n>20- d<n><n>21- 26.7<n><n>22- c<n><n>23- a<n><n>24- c<n><n>25- e<n><n>26- c<n><n>27- e<n><n>28- d<n><n>20-a<n><n>27-e<n><n>28-d<n><n>27-a<n><n>28-ad<n><n>30-e<n><n>31-a<n><n>1.1<n><n>    1-80 16 minutes = 200 seconds<n><n>1-80 + 16 = 200<n><n>8+20 = 28<n><n>8+2 =20 <n><n>8+8 =16<n><n><n>      6 + 6 = 12<n> <n>5+6=11 <n><n>6 + 4 =10<n>       4 + 4 = 8<n><n><n>9+6=15<n><n>5+9=14<n><n>5+4 =9<n><n><n><n>200/18 = 11 hours<n>00<n>3*180<n>2/18 <n><n>###<n><n>### Output:<n><n>a<n>a<n>b<n>e<n>b<n>b<n>c<n>a<n>a<n>a<n>e<n>a<n>a<n>d<n>a<n>a<n>c<n>

To forecast the population in 100 years for this town, which of the following would YOU NOT want to include in your forecast? A: the size of the town's population in the year 100 <n>B: the number of children in the town after 100 years  <n>C: the number of new immigrants into the town <n>D: the size of the population in the year 50 <n>E: the percent increase per year  <n>Note: the answer is not A B C or E.. it is <n>E in 10 years we can double the population again to 100<n>thus in 100 year we wil have total n population= 2x2 which is 4×100=400<n>Output:E<n><n>Input: What is the sum of the roots of 3 x 2 2 x 3  and 4 x 5?<n><n>Output: 144<n><n>Input: We have a rectangular piece of land. ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: a man cycling along the road noticed that every 18 minutes a bus overtakes him and every 6 minutes he meets an oncoming bus. if all buses and the cyclist move at a constant speed, what is the time interval between consecutive buses? Choices:  A: eyes B: biology laboratory C: shower stall D: old cheese E: decaying matter<n>Output:		C<n><h5 style="color: white"><n>Answer:<n><h5 style ="color: white"><n>    <h4 class="answer"><n>        <p style="color: white;"> D : old cheese<br><n>    </h4><n></h5><n><h5 style "color: white"><n>  <h4 class="correct answer"><n>    <p style="color white"> D : old cheese<n><n>Answer :<n><n>The time taken by buses to overtake in the given input is 18 minutes hence 6 + 18 = 24 minutes.<n><n>Therefore, 24 * 2 / 6 + 24 * 5 = 5 minutes.<n><n>Closest option is "6"<n><n>Example: (C) A: No, fungus can not grow on something made of milk. It is too moist and warm.<n><n>(D) E: Decaying matter<n><n>The cows that made the milk dung are more likely to grow fungus in a rotting cow carcass, but that is another story.<n><n>Example: (A) C: Milk does not usually create the optimal conditions for mushroom and fungi growth, except under the rarest of circumstances. When the temperatures are low, and it is cold and wet, mushrooms can begin to grow on milk. However the majority of the conditions that mushrooms grow in will be toxic to humans, including: animal manures, horse manure, poultry manure, and human manure.<n><n>Example: (E) D<n><n><h5 style = "color:white"><n>    <h3 class="solution"><n><n>        <p style = "color : white;"><n>            Correct : The time taken by buses is 18 minutes.<n><n>        </p><n><n>    </h3><n><n></h5>
